            <p>Here's something I've been studying.</p>

            <div class="myth-reality">
                <p><strong>Myth:</strong> "Organic traffic takes 6–12 months to build."</p>
                <p><strong>Reality:</strong> If engineered correctly, you can have qualified search traffic flowing in 2–3 weeks.</p>
            </div>

            <p>Here's why most brands fail at organic:</p>

            <p>They follow the traditional playbook:</p>

            <div class="step-list">
                <div class="step-item"><span class="step-number">1.</span> Write blog posts (weeks 1–4)</div>
                <div class="step-item"><span class="step-number">2.</span> Hope Google indexes them (weeks 5–8)</div>
                <div class="step-item"><span class="step-number">3.</span> Wait for rankings (months 2–6)</div>
