            <p>That's not luck. That's engineering.</p>

            <p class="section-title">Here's the key difference:</p>

            <p><strong>Traditional organic</strong> = hope-based (write content, hope it ranks, hope it converts)</p>

            <p><strong>Engineered organic</strong> = outcome-focused (identify keywords, build conversion-optimized content, measure results)</p>

            <p>Most agencies teach the first approach. I'm exploring the second.</p>

